# Patrol behavior — a minimal on-tick handler the ToolRegistry's compile
# pipeline accepts today. The long-form 5-verb Aether Behavior DSL (task #83,
# U07) is intentionally richer; we pin the minimal handler here so the
# InMemoryBackend compile path (script.compile) exercises the real registry
# dispatch without dragging in the full DSL type-checker. Swap the line below
# for a full `behavior patrol_v1 { ... }` block once the agent-cp backend's
# `wire` feature routes through aether-behavior-dsl.
on tick do move "forward"
